Spaghetti Sauce

Ingredients
½ medium size onion grated (large hole)
3 cloves garlic (crushed)
1 handful of fresh basil, cut into small short ribbons
   (if using dried...use a lot!)
1 large can crushed Roma tomatoes (this is key!)
Pinch of oregano
Pinch of thyme

Instructions
1. Sauté onions and garlic on medium heat (5) until onion is translucent.
2. Add basil, and sauté for approximately 1 minute.
3. Add crushed tomatoes.
4. Add pinch of oregano and thyme (optional).
5. Bring mixture to a boil, and then reduce to a simmer.
6. Simmer for 30 minutes.
